	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok pvp is very difficult at low levels with bards, and hard against warriors because they can get their resists so high you can spend tons of time killing them. also hard against wizzys unless you can get stuns off to every single spell they start, which is hard, since the first time i dueled i didn't have my spell graphics on.<br><br>Ok chants normally don't stick on players. But, if you are playing someone who has bad equip, obviously they have no resists and can be chanted. The slow song is completely useless, it VERY rarely sticks and last so short its not worth it, use the speed song. If you are indoors, avoid dueling and pvp.<br><br>If you want to melee, only do that against casters. Its better to mez, use a dot or 2, mez again, especially at higher levels when most spells take about 5 to 7 secs to cast, and mez only takes 3, so you can easily mez before a spell gets off, watch out for resists. If you are fighting a caster with shadow step, try to keep them mezzed, stack dots and continue mezzing, everytime mez wears off its kind of a supprise, and some songs can do about 100 to players, total, so if you stack 3 then you can seriously drop caster life. <br><br>Hardest to kill are paladins and shadowknights, they both deal big dmg with hits, and they have good abilities, like slow( a lasting slow) and root, in cases like this try mezzing first, if they have high resists, try to use the shadow step song while stacking dots, and staying out of range, or maybe just running, or giving up the duel. Rangers arn't so hard, they don't seem to have as much ac, hp, or resists that most classes have, so they are only moderatly difficult.<br><br>There yah go my oppinion on dueling<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
