	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10382414709526><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=10382414709526>RE: Newbie Armour for a Vah Shir bard</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=10382414709526#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Scholar>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>595 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 25th 11:47 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.44]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>HP is about the most important stat for everybody. Especially bards since our songs often draw aggro like honey draws flies.&nbsp;&nbsp;You think clerics and enchanters have aggro managment problems?  Bards have it just as bad if not worse.  So, go for AC and go for HP.  If you can get CHA and DEX up that helps, too.<br><br>In terms of earning your own way, there is a quest for some AC 16 leather tunic with nice stat buffs for a newbie you can do in Shar Val: <br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=1599" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=1599</a><br><br>This is easy to do, just a bit time consuming.<br><br>Next move is to get out of Shar Val and head to East Commons.  Farm all the spiderling silks and Low Quality or better hides you can get (you can still get exp from this a level 6).  Find a PC smith and offer to trade stacks of this stuff for Fine Steel Plate.  That's what I did. I had a full suit by the time my Vah Shir bard was level 14.  It has the same AC as lambent (which is overrated since Velious came out). <br><br>Smiths use the LQ hides and silk threads from spiderling silk to make leather padding for various plate armors.  I have seen smiths pay 1pp each for spiderling silks (although that is high). If you are a tailor of skill 30 you can make your own leather padding and sell those for 6pp each.<br>&nbsp;<br>Slipskin,47 Rogue<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br>Mewse,25 Bard<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a><br>Arcturos,29 Monk<br>Bertoxolous Server</td></tr>
