	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just wanted to add that you might want to keep in mind about the stats/ aggro discussion that bard tactics change with the lvl.<br><br>E.g. once you get your mana charm song you would even love to have more int to keep going on and on.<br><br>And don't emphazise str too much (remember you are bard anyways). Later on you are not tanking anymore (why? just take a look what you can do with your buffs and playing an instrument). Just keep some to carry that loot.<br><br>Aggro is a big problem if you are fighting in a group. Even if you think you are almost as good as a tank in the early lvls, just stay back for the first (couple of) combat rounds playing some buffs. It's a bit tricky to get the timing when to engage yourself.<br>Hey, but what fun would be left if the talent of a bard could be jugded by her stats?<br>&nbsp;<br>Wara Fairytune<br>Woodelf Bardess from Kelethin/Sol Ro<br>52 songs available at your local dealer!<br>New Horizon</td></tr>
