	   <tr><td colspan=2>Bards get a charm song at level 28.&nbsp;&nbsp;When you charm a monster it becomes your pet; temporarily. It doesn't last long but when it wears off you can try to recharm it.  Usually, that works fine.  You can then give the monster the standard pet commands.  Using charmed monsters is a standard tactic of enchanters and mid-level bards while soloing or for crowd control.<br>&nbsp;<br>Slipskin,47 Rogue<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br>Mewse,25 Bard<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a><br>Arcturos,29 Monk<br>Bertoxolous Server</td></tr>
