	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.42]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>At level 5 the only instrument you need is a lute or mandolin.&nbsp;&nbsp;Either does the same job.  At level 6 get a drum.  You will eventually also need a brass instrument and a wind instrument. Each song that is not sung will need a instrument for best performance (no pun intended).  Some songs won't work at all without the correct instrument. So, you will have 4 different instruments in addition to weapons and armor to fill out your equipment needs.<br><br>Ultimately, the very best string instrument is the Lute of the Howler.  The best drum I am told is Drums of the Beast.<br><br>At level 5 the best place to level is your local newbie zone.  The best place to level varies from level to level. So, I can't really give you a better answer.  You don't mention what city your bard is in now.  Personally, I liked Greater Feydark until level 8.  Then I went by boat to East Commons and West Commons until level 17. Then I went to North Karana &amp; High Hold Pass until level 20.  Spent 2 levels in Paludal Caverns in Luclin.  Just dinged 23 in Maru Seru and Netherbian Lair last nite wtih my bard.<br>&nbsp;<br>Slipskin,47 Rogue<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br>Mewse,25 Bard<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a><br>Arcturos,29 Monk<br>Bertoxolous Server</td></tr>
